Most of those shot on the square were hurling rocks at the troops and people close to their front lines. Thousands fled from the square, where hundreds of thousands of people had gathered to support students in the third week of a sit-in. Sporadic gunfire could still be heard on the outskirts of the square as troops shot at crowds of thousands. At 4:30 a. The square was in darkness. The troops cut a violent swath through the heart of Beijing to get to the the square, rolling through barricades and surging masses on the surrounding streets. Hundreds were wounded. 